Sentencas: Moisture effect on cathode behaviors is a major issue for solid oxide fuel cells servicing under severe high temperature environments.
Titulo: Moisture Effect on La0.8Sr0.2MnO3 and La0.6Sr0.4Co0.2Fe0.8O3 Cathode Behaviors in Solid Oxide Fuel Cells

Sentencas: This work studies the effect of dry air and moist air on La0.8Sr0.2MnO3 (LSM821) and La0.6Sr0.4Co0.2Fe0.8O3 (LSCF6428) cathodes at 800 degrees C by investigating the interfacial reaction and degradation through an AISI 441 interconnect/LSM821 (LSCF6428) electrode/yttria-stabilized zirconia (YSZ) electrolyte tri-layer structure.
Titulo: Moisture Effect on La0.8Sr0.2MnO3 and La0.6Sr0.4Co0.2Fe0.8O3 Cathode Behaviors in Solid Oxide Fuel Cells

Sentencas: Under the same processing condition, the grain size of the LSCF6428 cathode is smaller than that of the LSM821 cathode.
Titulo: Moisture Effect on La0.8Sr0.2MnO3 and La0.6Sr0.4Co0.2Fe0.8O3 Cathode Behaviors in Solid Oxide Fuel Cells

Sentencas: Ohmic resistance and polarization resistance of the cathodes are analyzed by deconvoluting the electrochemical impedance spectroscopy (EIS) results.
Titulo: Moisture Effect on La0.8Sr0.2MnO3 and La0.6Sr0.4Co0.2Fe0.8O3 Cathode Behaviors in Solid Oxide Fuel Cells

Sentencas: The LSCF6428 cathode has much smaller resistance than the LSM821 cathode.
Titulo: Moisture Effect on La0.8Sr0.2MnO3 and La0.6Sr0.4Co0.2Fe0.8O3 Cathode Behaviors in Solid Oxide Fuel Cells

Sentencas: Moisture produces a larger effect on the ohmic resistance and polarization resistance of the LSM821 cathode than on those of the LSCF6428 cathode.
Titulo: Moisture Effect on La0.8Sr0.2MnO3 and La0.6Sr0.4Co0.2Fe0.8O3 Cathode Behaviors in Solid Oxide Fuel Cells

Sentencas: More chromium diffuses from the interconnect to the cathode for both LSM821 and LSCF6428 electrodes thermally treated in moist air.
Titulo: Moisture Effect on La0.8Sr0.2MnO3 and La0.6Sr0.4Co0.2Fe0.8O3 Cathode Behaviors in Solid Oxide Fuel Cells

Sentencas: Based on the structure, elemental distribution, and EIS analysis, the interaction mechanisms between the electrodes and the AISI 441 alloy interconnect are proposed.
Titulo: Moisture Effect on La0.8Sr0.2MnO3 and La0.6Sr0.4Co0.2Fe0.8O3 Cathode Behaviors in Solid Oxide Fuel Cells
